    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI am using a language server that incorrectly advertises capabilities. When neovim sends a request that it cannot handle, the rejected request causes a hard error that makes the editor unusable. \n\nWhile this is the case for neovim, in vscode, the error is just logged, but the editor keeps going. \n\nEven though the incorrect advertisement of capabilities is clearly a bug in the language server, I feel like neovim should not punish its users like that, for two reasons:\n1. it's incoherent with vscode which makes language servers that are only tested with vscode behave in unexpected ways with neovim\n2. the language server rejecting requests is not a hard error in the sense that neovim cannot keep going. \n\nI would love to hear you opinions. Thank you for your consideration. \n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nbecause I do not want to add an entire implementation of an LSP here. This happens when editing `.cabal` files with `haskell-language-server`. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.3\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nhaskell-language-server 2.11.0.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 25.11\n\n### Log file\n\nn/a",
